<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 457
                    The Ambassador in Italy
                     (
                        Kirk
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State ad interim</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d457</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">457</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-06-30T10:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-06-30T10:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-30T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-30T10:00:00-05:00" n="457" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (<persName corresp="#p_B5">Bulgaria</persName>)/6–3045: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 457<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName>
                    </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss> ad interim</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-30T17:00:00+02:00">June 30, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2823. <persName corresp="#p_OMGWH1">Gen Oxley</persName> head Brit <gloss target="#t_del1">Del</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_ACC1">ACC</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_B5">Bulgaria</persName> (our 2814, June 29<note n="1" xml:id="d457fn1">See <ref target="#d456">documents Nos. 456</ref> and <ref target="#d693">693</ref>.</note>) reports he is informed Russian
                    division completed crossing of Danube at Ruse about three days ago and moved
                    southward towards Trinova and Shumen. <persName corresp="#p_OMGWH1">Oxley</persName>’s tentative estimate of Russian troops in Bulgar is ten
                        <gloss target="#t_divs1">divs</gloss> located roughly as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Two <gloss target="#t_divs1">divs</gloss> Varna Burgas; two <gloss target="#t_divs1">divs</gloss> Sliven Kotel area; one <gloss target="#t_divs1">div</gloss> between Yambol and Turk frontier; one
                                <gloss target="#t_divs1">div</gloss> Khaskovo Nomchilgrad; one
                                <gloss target="#t_divs1">div</gloss> Plovdiv area; one <gloss target="#t_divs1">div</gloss> along road south from Gorna Dzhumaya;
                            probably at least two <gloss target="#t_divs1">divs</gloss> north of
                            Balkan Mountains. General opinion is that there are now 200,000 Soviet
                            troops in Bulgar.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_OMGWH1">Oxley</persName>’s <gloss target="#t_msg1">msg</gloss> stated that in spite of doubtful veracity of many sources of
                        <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss> today, above is probably fair picture
                    of situation and it is impossible to obtain any more accurate <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
